.SS "INCOMPRESSIBLE DATA"
.sp
Files with already compressed data or with data that won\(cqt compress well with the CPU and memory constraints of the kernel implementations are using a simple decision logic\&. If the first portion of data being compressed is not smaller than the original, the compression of the file is disabled \(em unless the filesystem is mounted with \fIcompress\-force\fR\&. In that case compression will always be attempted on the file only to be later discarded\&. This is not optimal and subject to optimizations and further development\&.
.sp
If a file is identified as incompressible, a flag is set (NOCOMPRESS) and it\(cqs sticky\&. On that file compression won\(cqt be performed unless forced\&. The flag can be also set by \fIchattr +m\fR (since e2fsprogs 1\&.46\&.2) or by properties with value \fIno\fR or \fInone\fR\&. Empty value will reset it to the default that\(cqs currently applicable on the mounted filesystem\&.
