.SS "DRIVE FIRMWARE"
.sp
Firmware is technically still software but embedded into the hardware\&. As all software has bugs, so does firmware\&. Storage devices can update the firmware and fix known bugs\&. In some cases the it\(cqs possible to avoid certain bugs by quirks (device\-specific workarounds) in Linux kernel\&.
.sp
A faulty firmware can cause wide range of corruptions from small and localized to large affecting lots of data\&. Self\-repair capabilities may not be sufficient\&.
